<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2017/12/27/this-year-in-spring-2017">This Year in Spring - 2017</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon engineering"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/engineering">Engineering</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/fb22593caf24e4bb4c98d467cdd247e6?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<a class="author" href="/team/jlong">Josh Long</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2017-12-27 02:30:00.0">December 27, 2017</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="3133" href="/blog/2017/12/27/this-year-in-spring-2017#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>Hi Spring fans! Welcome to another, albeit very special, installment of <em>This Week in Spring</em>! This is the last installment before 2018 and so we’ll take the opportunity to review, as we always do in the last installment of the year, this very exciting year in Spring and its ecosystem.</p>
<p>Let me, on behalf of the Spring and larger Pivotal team, to be the first to wish you and yours a heartfelt happy and safe New Year! Let’s first look at some of the major trends that defined 2017. We’ve got a lot to cover!</p>
